bibata-studio
=============

This project is an independent reimplementation of the build pipeline for
Bibata cursor themes. It is NOT a fork of `github.com/ful1e5/bibata` (the
web application) in the git sense — no commit history is shared, and no
Python/TypeScript code is reused from that repository.

It DOES vendor artwork and build configuration from
`github.com/ful1e5/Bibata_Cursor` (a separate, asset-only repository by the
same author). Both upstream projects are licensed MIT.


VENDORED CONTENT
----------------

The following directories contain files copied verbatim from
`github.com/ful1e5/Bibata_Cursor` at commit `35ccfe2` (2024-06-18):

    src/bibata_studio/data/svg/groups/      372 SVG files (cursor artwork)
    src/bibata_studio/data/configs/         8 ctgen TOML build configs

These files are unmodified except for being relocated under the
`bibata_studio` package data directory so they install with the wheel.
They retain their upstream MIT license. Original copyright notice:

    MIT License
    Copyright (c) 2020 Abdulkaiz Khatri

    [full MIT text — see https://github.com/ful1e5/Bibata_Cursor/blob/main/LICENSE]


RUNTIME DEPENDENCIES (NOT VENDORED)
-----------------------------------

`clickgen` (https://github.com/ful1e5/clickgen, MIT, by the same author) is
imported as a pip package and drives the XCursor / Windows-cursor packing
stage. We invoke `clickgen.scripts.ctgen.main` in-process. No code from
clickgen is copied into this repository.

`resvg-py` (https://pypi.org/project/resvg-py/, MIT, unrelated maintainer)
provides the Rust-backed SVG rasterizer. Imported as a pip package.

`Pillow` is a transitive dependency of `clickgen`.


WHAT IS NOT FROM UPSTREAM
-------------------------

All Python source under `src/bibata_studio/*.py` and all tests under
`tests/*.py` were written for this project. The architectural decisions
(CLI surface, in-process clickgen invocation, HTML preview, Windows install
via `setupapi.dll`) are this project's own. The `ful1e5/bibata` web app
was consulted only as a reference for the cursor-recoloring protocol — the
agreement that SVGs use `#00FF00` for "base color", `#0000FF` for
"outline color", and `#FF0000` for "watch background color" placeholder
swatches.


